cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.DS

The paper discusses three projects related to programming language theory and mathematics, which suggests that the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The second project involves formal reasoning with nested and mutually inductive structures, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The third project involves the implementation of a type theory, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the first project involves a domain-specific language for financial contracts, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
